<TITLE> Law ministry splits </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, December 24 (bdnews24.com)  The law ministry has been split into two divisions in a bid to ease conflicts between its executive and judicial activities. A gazette published Wednesday announced that the ministry's two existing wings, the Law and Justice Wing and Legislative Drafting Wing, have been made separate divisions each to be headed by a secretary. Law minister Shafique Ahmed spoke of the proposal on Dec 17, saying the "the conflict between the executive and judiciary is an old one" and dividing the ministry would clear many of the problems. Law ministry spokesperson Mizanur Rahman said on Wednesday work towards division of the ministry had been in process at various levels of administration for some time. "It was recently approved in a secretary level meeting on reform of administration," he said. Before publishing the gazette ministry officials took the consent of president Zillur Rahman and prime minister Sheikh Hasina on a sum-up of the issue, a ministry official said. bd
